Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Zest and halve the @Lime{1}.

Trim and thinly slice the @Radishes{100}, then pop them into a #small bowl{}. Squeeze in half the lime, add the @Sugar for the Pickle{1} and season with @salt{}. Set your pickle aside.

Halve any thick @Tenderstem® Broccoli{150} stems lengthways, then pop them onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer and set aside for now.

Drain the @Firm Tofu{280%g} and cut widthways into slices (3 per person). Pat dry with #kitchen paper{}, then season with @salt and @pepper. Sprinkle over half the @Indonesian Style Spice Mix{1}.

> Press the spice mix in so it sticks.

Crack the @Egg{1} into a #medium bowl{} and whisk.

Put the @Panko Breadcrumbs{50%g} into another medium bowl, season with @Salt for the Breadcrumbs{1/4%tsp} and @pepper.

Dip the tofu into the egg, then the breadcrumbs, ensuring it's completely coated. Transfer to a clean #plate{}.

Pop a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add enough @oil{} to completely coat the bottom of the pan.

> TIP: You want the oil to be hot so the tofu fries properly - heat for 2-3 mins before you add the tofu.

Meanwhile, pop the broccoli on the middle shelf of your oven and roast until tender and crispy, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once the oil is hot, carefully lay the tofu into the pan, reduce the heat to medium-high and fry until golden-brown, ~{8-10%minutes} total. Turn every ~{2-3%minutes} and adjust the heat if necessary.

> TIP: Fry in batches if needed, adding more oil to the pan if it's looking dry.

Transfer the tofu to a plate lined with kitchen paper.

== Satay Sauce ==

While the tofu fries, pop a medium saucepan on medium-high heat.

Add the @Coconut Milk{200%ml}, @Peanut Butter{30%g}, @Sambal Paste{15%g}, @Ketjap Manis{25%ml}, @Sugar for the Sauce{1/2%tsp} and remaining Indonesian style spice mix. Stir to combine.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from the heat and add a squeeze of lime juice.

== To Serve ==

When everything's ready, add the lime zest to the rice and fluff up with a #fork{}. Share it out between your #bowls{}.

Top with the crispy tofu, roasted broccoli and pickled radishes.

Spoon the satay sauce over the crispy tofu to finish.

Enjoy!